Prerequisites:
1. This is for MAC only at this point. 
2. VSCode - Installed
3. Add Arduino Extension to VSCode

Add ESP32 board package for VSCode Arduino extension:
1. Open Arduino Extension.
2. Goto Settings and under Arduino additional URL’s add below URL’s
    1. https://raw.githubusercontent.com/espressif/arduino-esp32/gh-pages/package_esp32_index.json
    2. http://arduino.esp8266.com/stable/package_esp8266com_index.json
3. Press F1 and type “>Arduino: Board Manager” and select Board Manager.
4. Click Refresh package Indexes
5. Search for ESP32 and install latest version of ESP32 libraries


Creating Arduino Project in VSCode:
1. Open VSCode
2. Create new folder and open it in VSCode
3. Add file_name.ino to the project. 
4. Press F1 and type “Board Config” and select board as desired.. in my case it is Nano32 -> This should associate Arduino Extension to your project. 
5. Press Arduino Upload button. It it should auto create c_cpp_properties.json file which key for this project. 
